message.content:
Before Cam broke his right arm, he was able to type 9 words per minute on his phone. This means that in 5 minutes, he would be able to type 45 words (9 x 5).
After he broke his arm, he had to use his left hand for a while, and he could only type 6 words per minute. This means that in 5 minutes, he would be able to type 30 words (6 x 5).
The difference between the number of words Cam could type before and after breaking his arm is 15 words (45 - 30). Therefore, Cam's typing speed decreased by 15 words per minute after breaking his right arm.
